The paper presents a neural network-based approach for open set recognition, which involves classification of instances from unknown classes. This problem is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer security and cryptography (cs.CR), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Given that the paper proposes a neural network-based representation, cs.LG and cs.NE are the most likely sub-categories. However, since the problem of open set recognition is also relevant to computer security and computer vision, cs.CR and cs.CV are also likely sub-categories. Finally, since the paper involves developing a new approach for addressing a specific problem, cs.AI is also a possible sub-category.
